[thinking] **Evaluating metadata in tests**
[thinking] 
[thinking] The user is asking about improving coverage in testing. Typically, tests assess behavior after generating metadata, but I wonder if we should avoid failing hard when a resource isn't in the image. Native tests are expected to pass with the existing metadata. They don’t want to modify metadata directly. I’m thinking maybe we’ll regenerate the metadata before running the native tests in the workflow. For PR tests, empty metadata could lead to failures if we assert resource non-null, so I suggest not asserting that.
[thinking] 
